cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Recusal in your work, please cite it."
title: "Recusal: deterministic separation-of-powers governance for AI agents"
abstract: >-
  Recusal is a lightweight, zero-dependency, Claude-native library that places an
  independent, deterministic verifier in an autonomous agent's action path — one that can
  refuse to certify a tool call before it runs. The thing that generates the work must
  never be the thing that certifies it: no model sits in the decision path, so a verdict
  is replayable and auditable, including the refusal.
type: software
authors:
